  "prompt": "What are the best book in preparation for bank exams?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a strategic approach, including the right choice of study materials. Here\u2019s a list of some highly recommended books across different subjects commonly tested in bank exams, along with a brief description of each:\n\n### General Aptitude and Reasoning\n\n1. **\u201cA Modern Approach to Verbal and Non-Verbal Reasoning\u201d by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - A comprehensive book covering a wide range of topics in reasoning, suitable for both verbal and non-verbal sections.\n\n2. **\u201cQuantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\u201d by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - Covers all essential topics with plenty of practice problems and explanations.\n\n3. **\u201cLogical Reasoning: A Competitive Exam Approach\u201d by Nirmal Sinha**\n   - Focused on logical reasoning techniques and practice.\n\n### English Language\n\n1. **\u201cEnglish Language and Comprehension\u201d by A. K. Singh**\n   - Useful for improving grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension skills.\n\n2. **\u201cWord Power Made Easy\u201d by Norman Lewis**\n   - A great resource for building vocabulary crucial for English sections in bank exams.\n\n### Banking Awareness and Current Affairs\n\n1. **\u201cBanking Awareness\u201d by Kiran Publication**\n   - Encompasses key concepts related to banking, finance, and current affairs specifically tailored for bank exams.\n\n2. **\u201cCurrent Affairs Yearly\u201d by Kumar Prakashan**\n   - A comprehensive approach to covering major current events throughout the year.\n\n### Computer Knowledge\n\n1. **\u201cObjective Computer Awareness\u201d by R. Gupta**\n   - Focuses on fundamental computer concepts as well as the latest technologies and applications.\n\n### Miscellaneous\n\n1. **\u201cGeneral Knowledge 2023\u201d by Manohar Pandey**\n   - A useful resource for general knowledge and current affairs that complement other subjects.\n\n2. **\u201cBank PO Preliminary & Main Exam 2021: Quantitative Aptitude, Reasoning & English\u201d by Disha Experts**\n   - Targeted preparation for the various sections encountered in PO exams.\n\n### Mock Tests and Previous Year Papers\n\n1. **\u201cBank Exams: Guide to Objective Type Questions\u201d by Vikas Kumar**\n   - Contains previous years' questions and detailed solutions.\n\n2. **Online Mock Test Series**\n   - It's also essential to practice through online mock tests that simulate the actual exam environment. Websites like Oliveboard, Testbook, and Gradeup offer excellent practice sets.\n\n### Study Strategy\n\nIn addition to reading these books, make sure to:\n- **Create a Study Plan:** Allocate time for each subject according to your strengths and weaknesses.\n- **Practice Regularly:** Make use of problem sets and mock exams to improve speed and accuracy.\n- **Revise Frequently:** Regular revisions are crucial to retaining information.\n\nChoose the books that best fit your study style and enhance your preparation for bank exams. Good luck!",
